==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Burner
<hw>Burn"er</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who,
or that which, burns or sets fire to anything.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The part of a lamp, gas fixture, etc., where the
flame is produced.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Bunsen's burner</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <cd>see
<er>Bunsen burner</er>.</cd> -- <mcol><col><b>Argand burner</b></col>,
<col><b>Rose burner</b></col></mcol>, <cd>etc. See under
<er>Argand</er>, <er>Rose</er>, etc.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Burnet</ent>⟦br⟧
